Instrument marks
================

Instrument marks appear as instrument names in the left margin of your score.

Creating instrument marks
-------------------------

Use context tools to create instrument marks:

<abjad>
violin = contexttools.InstrumentMark('Violin ', 'Vn. ')
</abjad>

<abjad>
violin
print repr(violin) <hide
</abjad>

Attaching instrument marks
--------------------------

Attach instrument marks like this:

<abjad>
staff = Staff("c'4 d'4 e'4 f'4")
</abjad>

<abjad>
violin.attach_mark(staff)
</abjad>

<abjad>
show(staff)
iotools.write_expr_to_ly(staff, 'instrument-marks-1')
</abjad>


Example
-------

Use context tools to add instrument marks:

<abjad>
flute_staff = Staff("c'8 d'8 e'8 f'8")
violin_staff = Staff("c'8 d'8 e'8 f'8")
staff_group = scoretools.StaffGroup([flute_staff, violin_staff])
score = Score([staff_group])
contexttools.InstrumentMark('Flute ', 'Fl. ')(flute_staff)
contexttools.InstrumentMark('Violin ', 'Vn. ')(violin_staff)
</abjad>

Instrument marks appear as context settings in LilyPond input:

<abjad>
f(score)
</abjad>

Instrument marks appear as instrument names in notational output:

<abjad>
show(score)
iotools.write_expr_to_ly(score, 'instrument-marks-2') <hide
</abjad>
